# ForeShift Backend Spec

Read `cursor.md` for full context. Source: `ForeShift_Backend_Service_Spec.pdf`.

## Non-negotiables

- **Standalone REST API** — JSON in/out, curl-testable; never couple to Bubble internals.
- **Owner-editable coefficients** — event affinity, event magnitude, weather affinity; no hardcode, no redeploy to change.
- **Terminology:** "zone demand" only — never "restaurant demand".

## Formula (§2)

```
final = MIN( (base_score + event_lift) * weather_factor , 150 )
event_lift     = SUM( magnitude × concept_event_affinity × proximity ) per event
weather_factor = 1 - (weather_severity × concept_weather_affinity)
```

Additive events, multiplicative weather, cap 150, re-band. Must pass worked example → **45.38 / Moderate** with dummy coeffs.

## APIs

- `POST /zone-demand` — pure math (spec §3): zone, concept, day, daypart, events[], weather_severity
- `POST /ai/ask` — Phase 2 AI narration pipeline (implemented)

## Coefficient tables (dummy until owner loads real)

- Event affinity: all concepts **0.50**
- Event magnitude: Major stadium game **50**, Concert **30**, Festival **20**, Minor **10**
- Weather affinity: all concepts **0.35**

## Bands

Exceptional 110–150 | Peak 85–109 | High 65–84 | Moderate 40–64 | Light 20–39 | Minimal 0–19
